<subSubSection pageId="39" pageNumber="246" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="39.[178,1085,293,490]" pageId="39" pageNumber="246">
Comment: The original description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="PACE" authorityYear="1986" box="[654,781,293,315]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Atheta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pernitida">
<emphasis box="[654,781,293,315]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="246">N. pernitida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is based on a single female from &quot; 
<collectingCountry box="[243,316,322,343]" name="Myanmar" pageId="39" pageNumber="246">Burma</collectingCountry>
, Kalaw&quot; (
<bibRefCitation author="PACE R" box="[419,536,322,344]" pageId="39" pageNumber="246" pagination="427 - 468" refId="ref22166" refString="PACE R. (1986): Aleocharinae della Thailandia e della Birmania riportate da G. de Rougemont (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). - Bollettino del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Verona 11 [1984]: 427 - 468." type="journal article" year="1986">PACE 1986</bibRefCitation>
). Originally described in the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="THOMSON, 1858" authorityName="THOMSON" authorityYear="1858" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Atheta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[903,969,322,343]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="246">Atheta</emphasis>
THOMSON, 1858
</taxonomicName>
, it was moved to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="PACE" authorityYear="1987" box="[411,504,351,372]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Nepalota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[411,504,351,372]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="246">Nepalota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="PACE R" box="[543,673,352,374]" pageId="39" pageNumber="246" pagination="457 - 523" refId="ref22403" refString="PACE R. (2004): Hygronomini e Athetini della Cina con note sinonimiche (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae). - Revue Suisse de Zoologie 111 (3): 457 - 523." type="journal article" year="2004">PACE (2004)</bibRefCitation>
, who recorded it from Sichuan based on a single female. It was once again moved to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="PACE" authorityYear="1987" box="[646,739,381,402]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Nepalota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[646,739,381,402]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="246">Nepalota</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="PACE R" box="[781,913,381,403]" pageId="39" pageNumber="246" pagination="343 - 408" refId="ref22438" refString="PACE R. (2006): Aleocharinae del Nepal al Naturkundemuseum di Erfurt (Insecta: Coleoptera: Staphylinidae). - In: HARTMANN M. &amp; J. WEIPERT (eds.), Biodiversitat und Naturausstattung im Himalaya II. - Erfurt: Verein der Freunde und Forderer des Naturkundemuseums Erfurt e. V.: 343 - 408." type="book chapter" year="2006">PACE (2006)</bibRefCitation>
, who reported it from 
<collectingCountry box="[235,298,410,432]" name="Nepal" pageId="39" pageNumber="246">Nepal</collectingCountry>
, again based on a single female. The record from Sichuan most likely refers to the externally similar 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pace" authorityYear="1998" box="[437,562,439,461]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Nepalota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="globifera">
<emphasis box="[437,562,439,461]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="246">N. globifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, if in fact 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pace" authorityYear="1998" box="[678,804,439,461]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Nepalota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="globifera">
<emphasis box="[678,804,439,461]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="246">N. globifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="PACE" authorityYear="1986" box="[858,983,439,461]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Atheta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pernitida">
<emphasis box="[858,983,439,461]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="246">N. pernitida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
represent different species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
